-- Manchester United Beats Liverpool 2-1 to Extend League Lead
-- B y   J a m e s   C o n e
-- 2013-01-13T15:26:50Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-01-13/manchester-united-beats-liverpool-2-1-to-extend-league-lead.html
Manchester United stretched its lead
in English soccer’s Premier League to 10 points with a 2-1 win
against Liverpool at Old Trafford.  Second-place Manchester City can cut the gap back to seven
points with a win against Arsenal in today’s other game.   Robin van Persie and Nemanja Vidic got goals for United,
with  Daniel Sturridge  replying for Liverpool.   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
James Cone at 
 jcone@bloomberg.net  